The article discusses the hypocrisy of Democrats who are now opposing the Tax Cuts & Jobs Act, despite previously expressing support for tax reform. The author highlights statements made by Democratic leaders, including Chuck Schumer and Nancy Pelosi, in favor of easing the tax burden on the middle class. The article also mentions other Democratic senators and representatives who have called for tax reform in the past. The Tax Cuts & Jobs Act includes provisions to cut individual tax rates for low- and middle-income Americans, double the standard deduction, and repeal the individual mandate tax of Obamacare. The bill also aims to slash the corporate tax rate to 20 percent. The author questions whether Democrats will help Congress fulfill its promise to the public.